Zimbabwe's Exports of Minerals More Than Doubled Last Year, Herald Reports

-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 
2011-03-10T09:07:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-10/zimbabwe-s-exports-of-minerals-more-than-doubled-last-year-herald-reports.html
  Zimbabwe ’s mineral exports more
than doubled to $1.3 billion in 2010, the Herald said, citing a
report from the country’s Chamber of Mines.  Shipments rose from $600 million a year earlier, the
Harare-based newspaper cited the report as saying.  The country exported $409 million worth of platinum last
year, $380 million of gold, $134 million of ferrochrome, $111
million of nickel and $87.9 million worth of coal, the Herald
said. The report excluded diamonds, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Durban,  South Africa  at 
 blatham@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
